“I am led by my ancestors, my community, and artists before me who have helped pave the way for me to achieve my goals and dreams.” Get to know (and get inspired by!) @skyeeblu, an LA-based creative whose passion for her family, community culture and the arts drives her to support organizations like @FeedBlackFutures, founded in 2020 as a means to create sustainable change for Black food autonomy.

On behalf of Skye, together with @Converse, we’ve donated $5k to Feed Black Futures. Head to our #UOCommunity page at the link in bio to learn more about Skye, and tap to shop her faves from Converse! @omarskeeze @brinnnaa
🎶: “Fictional State of Mind” by @luketylershelton

node.text:
NYC chef and TikTok creator Nasim Lahbichi (@lahbco) makes “food that looks good and makes you feel good.” This Thursday, 4/22, he and @morganlynzi will be hosting an Instagram Live to cook a recipe from Nasim’s exclusive zine available exclusively at UO!

Pass the Plate features ten recipes from Nasim and chef Linda Thach (@iloveyourrainbow) with photos taken by @anishaspice and, as a bonus, 100% of proceeds from the zine will be donated to East NY Farms, a project that works to address food justice, with an additional $10,000 donation from UO.

Tune in to watch this week at 7pm on Thursday, and head to the link in bio to pick up your physical or digital copy of Pass the Plate!
